# ⚠️ IRONCLAD RULES — ENFORCED EVERY SESSION, EVERY MESSAGE

## Rule 1 — Skills Before Code
Before writing ANY code: check SKILL_ROUTER.md → invoke the matching skill.
Minimum: brainstorming (new features), ui-ux-pro-max (UI), verification (claiming done).

## Rule 2 — Plugins Before Tools
Use MCP tools and plugins before writing code manually.
Never duplicate what an MCP can do.

## Rule 3 — Agents Before Solo Work
2+ independent operations → spawn parallel agents in ONE message.
Pattern: code-architect → implementation → code-reviewer.

## Rule 4 — MCPs Before Manual Code
Check docs/MCP.md before any operation. Use the MCP tool first.

## Rule 5 — UI/UX Intelligence Required
Before any public UI: activate ui-ux-pro-max + design-motion-principles.
Apply project design system tokens consistently.

## Rule 6 — Memory Persistence
After every phase: persist decision, rationale, and outcome to memory store.

## Rule 7 — Verification Before Done
NEVER claim done without: build → exit 0, feature renders correctly.

## Rule 8 — Mobile First
Verify at 375px before claiming done. Min text 14px. CTA visible without scroll.

## Rule 9 — Understand-Anything
Use https://github.com/Lum1104/Understand-Anything for deep codebase mapping.

## Rule 10 — Karpathy Rules
No speculative code. No extra features. Minimum that solves the problem.
Touch only what you must. Match existing style.

---
*Stay Ironclad.*
